obo:BFO_0000066  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2781  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"NRG2 is essential for maturation of glutamatergic synapses\"\n- \"The late Dox treatment completely suppressed the developmental increase in AMPA-EPSCs and partially suppressed the NMDA-EPSCs to ~40% of the control (Fig. 4A,C1)...Developmental increase of the AMPA/NMDA ratio in newborn GCs was abolished by knock-down of NRG2 (Fig. 4C2).Because nascent glutamatergic synapses express only NMDA receptors and then AMPA receptors are added as they are matured, the AMPA/NMDA ratio is an index for maturity of glutamatergic synapses (Wu et al., 1996; Akerman and Cline, 2006; Haas et al., 2006). These results indicate that NRG2 is essential for the maturation of glutamatergic synapses in newborn GCs.\"\n\nFig.7: \"Effects of NRG2 depletion on glutamatergic synaptic transmission and dendritic arborization are rescued by NRG2-ICD overexpression\". Experimental description: The entorhino-hippocampi of postnatal day 6-9 (P6-P9) Sprague Dawley rat pups (Charles River) o" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2781" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

